9700 REM *** SHOOTING MINIGAME SUB-ROUTINE ***
9701 REM THE METHOD OF TIMING THE SHOOTING  		(LINES 6210 - 6240)
9702 REM WILL VARY FROM SYSTEM TO SYSTEM. FOR EXAMPLE, H.P.
9703 REM USERS WILL PROBABLY PREFER TO USE THE 'ENTER' STATEMENT.
9704 REM IF TIMING ON THE USER'S SYSTEM IS HIGHLY SUSCEPTIBLE
9705 REM TO SYSTEM RESPONSE TIME, THE FORMULA IN LINE 6240 CAN
9706 REM BE TAILORED TO ACCOMMODATE THIS BY EITHER INCREASING
9707 REM OR DECREASING THE 'SHOOTING' TIME RECORDED BY THE SYSTEM
9708 REM USING TIMER FUNCTION: HOUR TIMESTAM (IN SECONDS)
9709 REM SHOOTINGRESULT is a value [0..9]: The seconds it took you to shoot correctly: 0 means best, 9 means late or wrong. Difficulty gives you extra seconds to write.

9710 DIM GUNDICTIONARY$(5)
9711 GUNDICTIONARY$(0)  = "BOOM"
9712 GUNDICTIONARY$(1)  = "BANG"
9713 GUNDICTIONARY$(2)  = "BLAM"
9714 GUNDICTIONARY$(3)  = "POW"
9715 GUNDICTIONARY$(4)  = "WHAM"

9720 SHOOTINGWORDCHOICE = INT (RND (1)  * 4 + 1)

9730 TSDRAW = TIMER: REM add +2 if neccesary, tty too slow
9731 PRINT "TYPE " ;  GUNDICTIONARY$(SHOOTINGWORDCHOICE)
9732 INPUT RESPONSE$
9740 TSSHOOT = TIMER
9750 SHOOTINGRESULT = (TSSHOOT-TSDRAW) - (DIFFICULTYSHOOTING-1)
9751 IF ( UCASE$(RESPONSE$) <> GUNDICTIONARY$(SHOOTINGWORDCHOICE) ) THEN SHOOTINGRESULT=9
9752 IF ( SHOOTINGRESULT < 0 ) THEN SHOOTINGRESULT = 0
9753 IF ( SHOOTINGRESULT > 9 ) THEN SHOOTINGRESULT = 9
9754 REM PRINT "Shooting Result:"; SHOOTINGRESULT: 
9760 RETURN






9800 REM *** DATE SUBROUTINES ***
9801 REM Convert day counters into date variables
9802 REM Simplifications: 
9803 REM  - 1847 is NOT a leap year,
9804 REM  - IF (year MOD 4 = 0 AND year MOD 100 <> 0) OR (year MOD 400 = 0) THEN leap = 1

9810 REM --- Initialization ---
9811 REM Definir dias por mes en un array
9812 DIM daysOfMonth(12)
9813 RESTORE 9891
9814 FOR i = 1 TO 12 
9815 READ daysOfMonth(i)
9816 NEXT i
9817 REM IF leap = 1 THEN daysOfMonth(2) = 29
9818 RETURN

9820 REM Calculo de Mes, Dia del mes, Dia de la semana
9821 monthDay = COUNTERDAYS
9822 month = 1
9823 IF (monthDay <= daysOfMonth(month)) THEN GOTO 9830
9824 monthDay = monthDay - daysOfMonth(month)
9825 month = month + 1
9826 GOTO 9823

9830 REM Convertir Mes a Texto
9831 RESTORE 9892
9832 FOR i = 1 TO month 
9833 READ month$ 
9834 NEXT i

9840 REM Calcular Dia de la Semana
9841 REM IMPLEMENTAR Algoritmo Zeller simplificado o similar
9842 REM Usamos una formula de referencia para el dia 1 de enero del año 1847
9843 REM 1/1/1847 => Viernes (offset 5)
9844 RESTORE 9893
9845 FOR i = 1 TO (COUNTERDAYS +5) MOD 7
9846 READ weekday$ 
9847 NEXT i

9850 RETURN

